{"tid":1869740,"cid":4,"subCid":0,"title":"[Apple已死]加拿大實驗室測試   iPhone 11 Pro 輻射超標 137%","createTime":"2020-02-08T10:47:23.000Z","updateTime":"2020-02-09T08:04:08.000Z","uid":58335,"like":14,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":10,"replies":[{"pid":"94e6c6d2243d25207f76bb91b585258b28f2623e","tid":1869740,"uid":58335,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-08T10:47:23.000Z","msg":"iPhone 11 Pro 自從去年年底上市後，一直深受消費者歡迎，不過日前加拿大一間獨立實驗室發表的報告，則可能令對健康相當緊張的消費者打退堂鼓。專門進行電磁波測試的 RF Exposure Lab 對 iPhone 11 Pro 測試，結果輻射量超出法定數值。<br />\n<br />\n根據 RF Exposure Lab 的測試結果，iPhone 11 Pro 的 SAR 值（即 Specific Absorption Rate）達 3.8W/Kg，超過了美國聯邦通訊委員會 1.6W/Kg 的法定上限。SAR 是用作密實流動通訊產品中電磁波所產生的能量，對人體影響的衡量數據。相對寬鬆的歐盟標準是 2.0W/Kg，但 iPhone 11 Pro 在 RF Exposure Lab 的測試中仍然超標。<br />\n<br />\n至於超標 137% 是否會對人體造成嚴重傷害，這又未必，因為美國聯邦通訊委員會制定的標準相當保守，理論上在 50 倍以內的 SAR 都依然屬於安全。<br />\n<br />\n資料來源：appleinsider<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.eprice.com.hk/mobile/talk/4544/215125/1/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eprice.com.hk%2Fmobile%2Ftalk%2F4544%2F215125%2F1%2F&d=KH9yB5wEnJvJbT5Qn4WrOgqYqcROYCvJBJmaWwU8HGA%3D&h=162a90a5\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.eprice.com.hk/mobile/talk/4544/215125/1/</a>"},{"pid":"89b5b6243b4053a6953ad5507e557e15dfa1de2e","tid":1869740,"uid":94828,"like":13,"dislike":0,"score":13,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-02-08T10:49:44.000Z","msg":"idog擺部手機入褲袋肯定爛jj<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"c2d990cb55599afe9ffb524ad202ce4532db961a","tid":1869740,"uid":16447,"like":6,"dislike":0,"score":6,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-08T10:53:11.000Z","msg":"3.8 not great, not terrible"},{"pid":"33a8d22315f195750525526d979647fdfeafe790","tid":1869740,"uid":89514,"like":4,"dislike":4,"score":0,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-02-08T12:49:41.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},{"pid":"ced67e90d15c5ebac6e90dd96201d371a0da0a8e","tid":1869740,"uid":344307,"like":3,"dislike":1,"score":2,